What for ?
==========
This has C File which opens a file with O_SYNC|O_WRONLY|O_CREAT flags,
on the given file, and starts copying another file, "smallfile" to the
new file.

This write happen with O_SYNC properties.

Supporting script
=================
There is a "script.sh", which calls the executable of this C File,
with argument as "mount-point".

How to ?
=========
Compile the C File, cc -o write-osync-file write-osync-file.c
Execute "script.sh", with the mount point as argument

